spanGrp.span: ‘I saw in the computer that it showed what I saw.
Yís të pe tebeli_yaga nã í sũã'-je-ra mẽ-gẽ të sũã' yís të-ra
I first saw that there was a man on a tree.
Yís të primero í sũã' desãu rö pekaga katerinã rö (_) kaljula jãrga
He was fat and was up in tree bringing down fruits;
Pekaga rö ólë' kateröga je të kalwö bötse-gẽ
he put them into something; he filled up three of them.
jolõwe-gẽ-ne-ite ele dujali jãrga Bótsá-rö-ka-ite rö mãñã-l röga Shiwã'-wã-ite köũ
The man did not see that there was a boy coming on his bike; he was riding it really fast.
Pekaga tel rö ka wã í sunẽ ta nã peyaba jeyiwa dajũ nẽ e-gla tebeli_yaga inga ra jũr datse-nẽ tebeli_yaga inga
He went by and saw that they were full.
Kã'u-mĩ-ka kepa í të í sũã'-ra-nã dujalali rö shiwã
So, he took one, put in the front of his bike and left.
Je kueinga í të e-gla gugá-wã kagá-ite tebeli_yaga wötsõ Mẽnẽtse í wa
He was going far away, the loaded person was looking around.
Damĩu komĩ' je (m) të pe deli sũẽ-ra
The place was vast and nice.
pe kã' sigenã köũ bá rama
He then crashed against a girl who was coming on another bike.
Jekepa í kenã' ku peyaba alaglöwa dajũ mẽ e-gla tebeli_yaga inga mẽ
So his hat fell onto the ground;
Jekepa í sombrero shkö janã-mĩ jiski inga
it fell down and so did the fruits he had taken away from the man.
Je janã-mĩ jiski inga jekepa í wa pekaga kalwö betetsẽ kenã'u-mĩ í yiga mĩ jeska
Jeska nẽ peyabla jeyiwa dujali nẽ mãñã-l nẽ
I thought they were going to attack him;
Yís të í begetsá-nã je í be-gẽ-leirö
but they didn’t; instead they helped him put the fruits back into the basket.
ka wã í bugenẽ-nẽ ta Je të í kimã'-nẽ í kanasta shiwã'-wã-nẽ kalwö shkö í wa
He got back on his bike.
Jes/ kepa jẽk kaga-nẽ í tebeli_yaga inga nẽ
The three boys were walking away and found his hat;
Beteũ-te-nẽ peyabla jeyiwa tres shkö-nẽ (_) shköratse të í sombrero kwablá-nẽ
they pickt it up and one of them went to give it to him.
kagá-nẽ-ite Jeska e-gla mẽnẽ-nẽ ĩã í juã'-nẽ
So he gave him three fruits and hurried away.
Jeska pe/ (_) e-gla të kalwö mã'-nẽ ĩã mãñã-l nẽ Jeska junã'u-mĩ junã'u-mĩ
Next, the man was still on the tree;
kepa tögapanẽra pekaga kateröga kaljula nã
he had already filled up three baskets,
Je të tres ska… je të í kanasta mãñã-l shiwã'-wã-ka
so he decided to climb down to see them; so he did.
kueinga begetsá-ite í jẽk jawa-te-nẽ sũã Í jẽk jawa-te-nẽ
Once down one basket was missing; there were only two of them.
deu-nẽ jiski inga ra e-gla ka juenã ĩã solo bo-l bö dujali-nẽ
there was a bench behind him;
Jekepa kalwak kalu wa í teki mẽ
so he sat down on it to figure out what might have happened with the other full basket.
Jeska pekaga jẽk kájká-nẽ í begetsö-nẽ-nã mãga jera í kanasta kalu shi-wã kalwö ra
He did not know what had happened with them.
je ka juenã ĩã (_) mãga je de rö í
